# 🚀 Docker & Jenkins Setup on GCP VM

This project demonstrates **Docker installation, container management, NGINX deployment, and Jenkins setup** on a GCP Virtual Machine.

---

## ☁️ Step 1: Create VM on GCP

* Go to Google Cloud Platform
* Create a VM instance (Ubuntu recommended)
* Allow **HTTP (80)** and **Custom ports (8080 for Jenkins)**

---

## 🐳 Step 2: Install Docker

### Method 1: Using Script

```bash
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o install-docker.sh
sudo sh install-docker.sh
```

### Method 2: Using APT

```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
```

### Verify Installation

```bash
docker -v
docker ps
```

---

## 📦 Step 3: Basic Docker Commands

```bash
docker pull ubuntu
docker pull hello-world
docker images
docker ps
```

---

## 🌐 Step 4: Run NGINX Container

```bash
docker run -d --name vikash -p 80:80 nginx
```

👉 Access in browser:

```
http://<VM-IP>
```

---

## 📁 Step 5: Create Custom HTML Page

```bash
mkdir -p ~/docker-nginx/html
cd ~/docker-nginx/html
vi index.html
```

### Sample HTML

```html
<h1>Hello Vikash 🚀</h1>
<p>This is running inside Docker NGINX</p>
```

---

## 🔗 Step 6: Mount Volume to NGINX

```bash
docker run --name docker-nginx -p 80:80 -d \
-v ~/docker-nginx/html:/usr/share/nginx/html nginx
```

👉 Now your custom HTML is served via NGINX

---

## ⚡ Step 7: Run Multiple Containers (Testing)

```bash
for i in {1..30}; do docker run -d --rm alpine sleep 1000; done
```

---

## 🐧 Step 8: Run Interactive Containers

```bash
docker run -it ubuntu
docker run -it centos:7
```

---

## ⚙️ Step 9: Jenkins Setup in Docker

Run Jenkins container:

```bash
docker run -it -d -p 8080:8080 jenkins/jenkins:latest
```

👉 Access Jenkins:

```
http://<VM-IP>:8080
```

---

## 🔑 Get Jenkins Initial Password

```bash
docker ps
docker exec -it <container_id> cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword
```

---

## 📊 Useful Commands

```bash
docker images
docker ps -a
docker stop <container_id>
docker start <container_id>
docker rm <container_id>
docker logs <container_id>
```

